- lower case writing for function / variable
- upper case writing for constant macro / variable, ex : EIR_KER_INIT_ARRAY
- based prefix : eir_ (usually all public stuff)
- core renderer prefix : eir_gfx_
- api renderer prefix : eir_gfx_api_
- kernel prefix : eir_ker_
- core system prefix : eir_sys_
- target system prefix : eir_sys_os_
- maths prefix : eir_maths_
- core sound prefix : eir_snd_
- api sound prefix : eir_snd_api_
- core input prefix : eir_inp_
- api input prefix : eir_inp_api_
- core window prefix : eir_win_
- api window prefix : eir_win_api_
- begin with a simple main.c file, code only that is needed, use function a lot
- typedef struct begin finish by _t, ex: eir_gfx_env_t
